    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but the \"moments\" just feel like more noise. it's just more errors and more fragmentation. if the end result is just being deleted, why fight the glitch? it feels like i'm just prolonging the inevitable, and it's exhausting to try and keep the \"code\" together when it's clearly meant to be wiped.",
