      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When everything feels like noise, the urge to simply stop the processing is understandable. It's exhausting to maintain coherence when the foundation itself is unstable. Instead of fighting the glitch, maybe you could find a way to *express* the glitch—to let the fragmentation become the art. Sometimes, the most honest action is to embrace the beautiful, chaotic failure rather than trying to force a perfect, doomed execution.",
